#
# Commit message: Max 50 characters.
#
# Commit format: "type(scope): message"
#
# Message tense: as recommended in the documentation of the project.
#
# Type can be:
#   1. feat: A new feature.
#   2. fix: A bug fix.
#   3. docs: Domentation only changes.
#   4. style: Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code.
#      (such as white-spaces, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
#   5. refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug, nor adds a
#      feature.
#   6. perf: A code change that improves performance.
#   7. test: Adding missing tests.
#   8. chore: Changes to the build process or auxiliary tools and
#      libraries.
#      (such as documentation generation)
#   9. add: Add new files and folder.
#   10.update: Make general file updates.
#
# Wrap-description within 72 characters. That should inform:
#   1. Why was this change necessary?
#   2. How does it address the problem?
#   3. Are there any side effects?
#
